<section id="homepage_blurb" class="sixteen columns no-mar" >
    <div id="homepage_quotes" class="sixteen columns no-margin">
        <div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p><strong>&ldquo;I can speak freely because I am anonymous.</strong>
I don't have to worry about my words getting
back to a hospital administrator.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;Exciting doctor interaction, very helpful with difficult cases, very interesting social topics and discussions&hellip; It is <strong>a form of collective intelligence that allows individuals to achieve more than they could on their own.</strong>&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;Being a semi-anonymous environment actually allows for more <strong>honest and useful advice and comments</strong>.  I get enough daily BS, PC crap in real life.  I don't need more in the virtual life.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;You can&rsquo;t just Google medicine, you need a human source. We have to go beyond &lsquo;cookbook&rsquo; medicine, and seek <strong>reasonable, experienced minds to think through difficult and diverse cases</strong>.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;<strong>If it was real life, we&rsquo;d all hang out.</strong>&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;<strong>Diverse. Interactive. Interesting and also sometimes funny. One does not feel alone.</strong>&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;Medicine is fun, when it&rsquo;s without the intrusion of multiple third parties. <strong>We love posting cases on SERMO...</strong>we get to practice medicine even if we don&rsquo;t get paid for it.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;Doctors don't have the time to come to a real doctors' lounge any more. On SERMO we can ask questions and share our lives and frustrations. <strong>Whenever we feel stressed out, we come to get support and find it.</strong> Any time of the day.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;<strong>I actually shared a medical mistake for the benefit of my peers</strong> on SERMO...but would not have done so if I was identified.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;Regulators are forcing us to comply with rules and docs hardly get a voice. We&rsquo;re made to feel isolated and alone. It&rsquo;s overwhelming but <strong>SERMO is THE place where we can finally talk and feel like we are not alone.</strong> We know that we&rsquo;re all in the same boat.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;I think SERMO has nailed it. If I want to read a clinical discussion, I can do that. If I want to read something funny, I can do that. If I want to get into politics, I can do that. If I need help with a patient, I have a place to do that.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;<strong>Had I not read a post on SERMO, I would not have nailed the diagnosis.</strong>&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>"Medicine should have a unified world community. Despite political, cultural and ethnic differences, people have the same enemy: disease and everyday problems&hellip; <strong>I learned many things and have made many doc-friends.</strong> Thank you&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>&ldquo;These days <strong>doctors are super busy</strong> and don&rsquo;t have time to stop what they are doing and find a colleague with the appropriate expertise.&rdquo;</p></div><div class="wrapper quote"><h1>Why doctors love SERMO</h1><p>[SERMO] is the only forum that I know of that has been able to provide a <strong>safe atmosphere for us [doctors] to talk with each other in the same language</strong>. It has also been a place where I have felt welcome and received a lot of support when I have needed it.</p></div>    </div>
